http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#com.@value: This ontology models interpretive theories about Twin Peaks by separating narrative entities (Person, Place, Event, Realm) from theory-scoped claims. A Theory asserts one or more Claims. Each Claim isAbout a NarrativeEntity and may assign a RealityStatus or specify a dreamer (DreamerClaim). The design supports competing interpretations without forcing a single global truth.
Realm is a specialized kind of Narrative Entity.
